**__Write4Change Fall Applications__**

Fall applications for Write4Change (http://www.write4change.org/) are now open through **September 12th**!

**What is W4C?**
Write4Change is a collaborative authoring community of youth writers supported by a team of adult and youth moderators and researchers connected to the University of Pennsylvania’s Graduate School of Education.

**What do we do?**
Our mission is to create a community that fosters an open, safe environment for writers to share their creativity, passions, and support through writing. Whether it be through writing, joining the literary magazine, or performing research, we provide a place for passionate high schoolers to grow as writers. I have been doing Write4Change for one year now and have enjoyed meeting and collaborating with doctoral, graduate, and undergraduate students. As a senior, I have also learned a ton about writing college applications if college/university is a thing you want to do after high school. 

Currently, we are looking to recruit younger high school students (freshmen and sophomores). However, I just wanted to put this opportunity out there for you juniors. If you are interested in applying, you can contact me, <@worst minesweeper>, for more information and questions. Oh, and also, if you have any younger siblings in high school, feel free to share this idea with them too!

**DISCLAIMER:** this organization is **not** affiliated with Conestoga High School and meets outside of school hours.
